article.headline: TCU 64, Grambling State 46
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Ryan Wall scored 14 points and Alvardo Parker had 13 as TCU beat Grambling State 64-46 on Friday. Wall, Parker and Keion Micthem, who scored 11 points, all came off the bench to help TCU (4-1) reach its best start since 1998. In all, the Horned Frogs got 48 points from their substitutes, who logged the bulk of the minutes. Kendric Baker scored 16 points and Andre Ratliff had 13 for Grambling State (1-2), which shot just 29 percent from the field. Kevin Langford added 9 points and 6 rebounds for TCU.
